Package it.unibo.alchemist.boundary.wormhole.implementation

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractNSEWormhole2D
    AbstractNSEWormhole2D = Abstract with No Side Effects Wormhole2D.
    Partial implementation for the interface IWormhole2D.
    I am considering the particular case of the view as an entity into the sceern-space: the y-axis grows on the bottom side of the screen.
    AbstractSlideInputManager
    ASlideInputManager is the base class for any class whose aim is to handle the the sliding of any physical/virtual device/control.
    AngleManager
    An AngleManager converts the sliding of any physical/virtual device/control into an angle expressed with radians.
    DoubleDimension
    Implementation of the Dimension2D abstract class with double precision.
    ExpZoomManager
    An ExpZoomManager converts the sliding of any physical/virtual device/control into a zoom rate through an exponential function (in this way I am sure to not see negative values ;-).
    Zoom = base ^ (amount of slides / normalization value).
    LinZoomManager
    An LinZoomManager converts the sliding of any physical/virtual device/control into a zoom rate through a linear function.
    Zoom = amount of slides * rate.
    MapWormhole
    Wormhole used for maps rendering.
    NSEAlg2DHelper
    Utility class for 2D-vector operation.
    NSE = No Side Effects.
    NSEPointerVelocityHandler
    Implementation for IPointerVelocityManager interface.
    NSE = No Side Effects.
    NSEWormhole
    NSEWormhole2D = No Side Effects Wormhole2D.
    Complete implementation for the AbstractNSEWormhole2D class.
